Probably there were more than one present. but the death penalty was a precautionary measure to prevent the fraud which they practised upon the people from being divulged by the servi, the sacrifice of human victims being, doubtless, represented as an essential part of the ritual, as in the Herminonic ceremonial of the Semnones. Cp. ch. 39. The priests thus secured necessary help, and at the same time were free from all suspicion of foul play.
